snippet.textDisplay: Kenny tried but Kenny failed, I’m glad everyone who’s a fan of wilder thought Kenny would be the perfect ref, you guys were right, he was, he did everything he could to keep wilder in the fight, that just made it more clear that Tyson fury is the champion, deontay was holding onto Tyson as much as Tyson was holding him, deontay was trying to stay up the whole last two rounds by clinching, but like you guys said “Kenny won’t let you do that holding shit” and took a point away from fury. I honestly wanted the fight to go 12 rounds, I’m a fan of both of them, but watching the fight it was too blatantly obvious that Kenny was the ref to help deontay. I hate seeing that shit no matter who’s fighting no matter who I’m routing for, shits disgraceful. Kenny was holding out for deontay hoping deontay would land one right hook and end the fight instantly, I bet if Tyson got even clipped a little he would have skipped the 8 count and ended the fight. Dude looked like he was gonna cry when he was raising Tyson’s hand. If Fury got wobbled, Kenny Bayless would have jumped in real fast and  stopped it immediately, i have no doubt, yet he let wilder fight until wilder was a few punches from becoming adonis stevenson.
